This paper discusses a new routing mechanism for IoT networks, which involves communication between low-power devices over long distances via multi-hop transmissions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also analyzes the performance of the proposed mechanism based on graph theory, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper proposes reliability and delay models, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
